title: Live coverage: Starlink mission marks SpaceX’s 450th flight-proven Falcon booster launch
summary: The Starlink 10-30 mission will add 28 more satellites to SpaceX’s low Earth orbit megaconstellation. Liftoff of the Falcon 9 rocket from pad 40 at Cape Canaveral Space Force Station is set for 1:03 a.m. EDT (0503 UTC) on Monday.
